explanation.en:
Trick: "No Solution Ratio" - For no solution, $ rac{a_1}{a_2} =  rac{b_1}{b_2} 
e  rac{c_1}{c_2}$. Here, $ rac{3}{2k-1} =  rac{1}{k-1} 
e  rac{1}{2k+1}$. From $ rac{3}{2k-1} =  rac{1}{k-1}$: $3(k-1) = 1(2k-1) \Rightarrow 3k - 3 = 2k - 1 \Rightarrow k = 2$. Now check the inequality: $ rac{1}{k-1} 
e  rac{1}{2k+1}$. For $k=2$, $ rac{1}{2-1} = 1$ and $ rac{1}{2(2)+1} =  rac{1}{5}$. Since $1 
e  rac{1}{5}$, $k=2$ is the correct value.

explanation.hi:
Trick: "कोई हल नहीं अनुपात" - कोई हल न होने के लिए, $ rac{a_1}{a_2} =  rac{b_1}{b_2} 
e  rac{c_1}{c_2}$। यहाँ, $ rac{3}{2k-1} =  rac{1}{k-1} 
e  rac{1}{2k+1}$। $ rac{3}{2k-1} =  rac{1}{k-1}$ से: $3(k-1) = 1(2k-1) \Rightarrow 3k - 3 = 2k - 1 \Rightarrow k = 2$। अब असमानता की जाँच करें: $ rac{1}{k-1} 
e  rac{1}{2k+1}$। $k=2$ के लिए, $ rac{1}{2-1} = 1$ और $ rac{1}{2(2)+1} =  rac{1}{5}$। चूंकि $1 
e  rac{1}{5}$ है, $k=2$ सही मान है।

